name: Thu Tran
text: I’m usually not a big deep dish guy. But I really liked Rosati’s. We got the 10 inch pizza and it was enough for 3 of us. Good sauce. Highly recommend.

name: Kathy Beni
text:
Pleasantly surprised.  Tiny place with limited seat even if wasn't COVID-19.
Got thin crust, hamburger, mushrooms and onions, and 2 sodas <$25.  It took about 14 minutes, came with red pepper, parmesan cheese and salt packets if you wanted.  Good flavor on sauce, plenty of cheese.  Will try deep dish next time.

name: Gregory Packnett
text: As a native Chicagoan what I used to miss most was a good Italian beef sandwich. That is before Rosati’s opened. Great sandwich fixed the same way it was in Chicago. I suggest you have your sandwich dipped to really enjoy it  the way they do in the city.

name: Kelly Gordon
text: We had our order from Rosati’s Pizza delivered last night. The pizza, antipasto salad & Italian side salad were all delicious! Pizza was hot, salads chilled. Arrived earlier than projected time so we were super happy! We’re new to Waukee so we will be ordering again from Rosati’s!!

name: Matt Rawson
text: I know there's been some talk of some really poor service and I think you can have that anytime a new restaurant opens. Both of our experiences have been very pleasant. We tried the thin crust pizza the first time, then we did the thick crust on this visit. Both times the pizza was delicious and service was pretty darn good.

name: Jon Struve
text: We really enjoyed the pizza. Got the double dough pepperoni. We are new to town, wanted to try something local. Our only trouble with it was that it is extremely filling. There was a lot of cheese and dough, so both of those just kinda blew up your stomach. Super tasty, probably won’t get a large next time

name: Cookie And unicorn dolls
text: This is our second time ordering. In less than a week, lol, because it was so good the first time. Second time just as good.

name: Travis Miller
text: I was pleasantly surprised at how great this thim crust pizza was.  They also called to double check that I wanted extra pizza sauce which was a nice check (I ordered online).  It was ready in 30 mins (which is what they promised).  Look online for coupons before ordering (then give that savings as tip money to them).
